The Danmasanin Kano, Alhaji Yusuf Maitama Sule has died in Cairo hospital.

According to a statement signed by Alhaji N.A Shariff said that he died this Monday morning after a brief illness.

Yusuf Maitama Sule was born in Kano state and was a Nigerian politician, acclaimed orator and diplomat.

In 1976, he became the Federal Commissioner of public complaints, a position that made him the nation’s pioneer ombudsman.

			
